
CHECK_SIGNATURE (1)                 ROA-PKI                   CHECK_SIGNATURE(1)


NAME

        check_signature - checks the signature on a certificate or a CRL

SYNOPSIS   

        check_signature signedfile signerfile

DESCRIPTION
    
        The signature in the "signedfile" is checked using the public key in
        the "signerfile".  The type of contents in the "signedfile" are 
        designated by its suffix: ".cer indicates a certificate, and ".crl"
        indicates a CRL.

        Response messages:

          Usage: signed cert or CRL, signer's cert
          Signature succeeded
          Signature failed
          Can't get file ...
          Signature checking error in ...
          Invalid type ...
          Invalid algorithm ...

       where the ellipsis is replaced with specific information.
                             
